<p class="p">Variations among the maximum and minimum temperatures in the 2020–2049 period were determined in comparison with the 1976–2005 baseline period. Firstly, the delta ratio values (ΔT) of the maximum and minimum temperatures between the 30-year average monthly values were calculated for the upcoming period (2020–2049) and then the simulated baseline period (1976–2005) was calculated by the same model for each cell according to the following equation [
 <xref rid="pone.0218725.ref030" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">30</xref>]. These values estimate a 30-year average of climate change, as considered in relation to the baseline period. The baseline period refers to data belonging to 1976–2005 which can also be mentioned in the formula as the 'base.' 
